Due to impending weather conditions, the Hillsborough Township Board of Education will have an early dismissal today, Monday December 2, 2019. All afternoon Kindergarten and Pre-Kindergarten classes have been cancelled. All district after school activities have been canceled. Lunches will not be served. The Catholic Charities aftercare programs will be be closed. Children who attend Catholic Charities after school services will be sent home at dismissal time.

Thank you. Please stay safe.

post_text:
Due to the excessive heat that is predicted for tomorrow, Thursday, September 6, all Hillsborough Township Public Schools will have an early dismissal. All afternoon Kindergarten and preschool classes are cancelled. Please anticipate your afternoon bus (grades 1-12) arriving at the bus stop approximately 2 hours and 25 minutes earlier than regular dismissal. Kindergarten afternoon buses home will arrive approximately 20 minutes earlier.

Lunch will not be served. Catholic Charities after school programs are cancelled.

Your school principal will notify you of any additional changes to after school and evening events.

Please visit https://www.htps.us/dist_info/school_hours_and_closings to see your specific school dismissal time.

Thank you and please stay safe in the heat.
